qas.question: Which nicknames were used to form the conservative and liberal elements?
In which year was the body installed?

context: In the constituent legislature or convention, the conservative and liberal elements formed using the nicknames of <a0_0>Chirrines and Cuchas<a0_0/>. <a1_0>The military<a1_0/> entered as a third party. The elections for the first regular legislature were disputed, and it was not until May 1, <a2_0>1826<a2_0/>, that the body was installed. The <a3_0>liberals<a3_0/> gained control and the opposition responded by fomenting a conspiracy. This was promptly stopped with the aid of informers, and more strenuous measures were taken against the conservatives. Extra powers were conferred on the Durango governor, <a4_0>Santiago Baca Ortiz<a4_0/>, deputy to the first national congress, and leader of the liberal party.
